## Question 3: Corporate Login System (String Comparison) 
#**Scenario**: An internal business tool is only accessible to employees with the role of "Admin". 
#**Task**:

#- Ask the user to input their Job Role.
#- Convert the input to uppercase or lowercase to ensure case-insensitivity (e.g., "admin", "Admin", "ADMIN" should all work).
#- If the role matches "ADMIN", print: "Access Granted: Welcome to the Management Portal."
#- Else, print: "Access Restricted: User rights insufficient."

# Code for Question 3
jRole = input("Enter Job Role: ").lower()
if jRole == "admin":
    print("Access Granted: Welcome to the Management Portal.")
else:
    print("Access Restricted: User rights insufficient.")